I had an idea for a new small new feature that would be nice to have, but wanted to kick it around with other devs before putting it into the issue queue. It's within the scope of my coding ability, so if there's a warm reception to it I can clone the repository and do the work myself.

Michael Morris
2021-01-17 14:46:28

*Thread Reply:* This involves the setWorldConstructor method.

Michael Morris
2021-01-17 14:46:44

*Thread Reply:* Currently you simply give it a class and you're off to the races.

Michael Morris
2021-01-17 14:47:17

*Thread Reply:* My idea is to allow additional arguments which would be passed into each World that got created.

Michael Morris
2021-01-17 14:48:24

*Thread Reply:* Use case... My setup spawns hugo as a child process in node js and an express.js server. The tests have to talk to them, at least to reset them between tests.

Michael Morris
2021-01-17 14:49:29

*Thread Reply:* So I'd like to do: setWorldConstructor(UcxWorld, servers, i18n);

Michael Morris
2021-01-17 14:49:54

*Thread Reply:* Then: class UcxWorld(servers, i18n);

Michael Morris
2021-01-17 14:51:02

*Thread Reply:* This is a BC compatible change, but once there's a commitment to allow an open list of arguments follow the class argument to the function it becomes locked in.

Michael Morris
2021-01-17 14:51:39

*Thread Reply:* Any thoughts before I do a more formal write up?

Michael Morris
2021-01-17 14:53:10

*Thread Reply:* Also, I do have a current work around - simply making servers a global object. I dislike globals though.

Max

*Thread Reply:* So, for example, currently we do something like this in the feature file:

  Scenario: blah blah
    Given such and such
    When blah blah
    Then blah blah
    And such and such has the following data
      | maMtmPriceBPriceValuation.pricedOutIndicator   | true   |
      | fillVal.orderRef    | 21T1286382                        |
      | fillVal.val.valId   | 21T1286382-66-1

So, as you can see, paths like maMtmPriceBPriceValuation.pricedOutIndicator are used to assert the data you want. But if a field of maMtmPriceBPriceValuation is a List, like for example maMtmPriceBPriceValuation.pricingTermValuations is, then we would like to assert on all or some list elements of type PricingTermValuation as well. Julien Kronegg
2023-03-22 07:45:09

*Thread Reply:* Would you be interested in solving https://github.com/cucumber/cucumber-jvm/issues/2707 ?

#2707 Reduce build duration by lowering Mockito usage
<p><strong>ü§î What's the problem you've observed?</strong></p> <p>Mockito has a impact on the unit test execution time (seen using IntelliJ Profiler flame graph):</p> <p>Total build duration: 3min17 = 197 seconds<br /> Total test duration : 23.5 seconds<br /> Total Mockito contribution : 4.2 seconds (18% of tests, 2% of build duration)</p> <p>By reducing the usage of Mockito, the test duration can be lowered with two advantages:</p> <p>‚Ä¢ this gives the developer a shorter feedback loop. ‚Ä¢ the energy consumption is lower (green IT), which is important because the cucumber-jvm project is built often (due to PR and renovate bot). 2% is not a lot, but on the long term, it makes a difference.</p> <p><strong>‚ú® Do you have a proposal for making it better?</strong></p> <p>I didn't check in details, but for example in <code>JavaBackendTest</code>, the <code>@Mock</code> <code>ObjectFactory</code> and <code>Glue</code> could be replaced by fake implementations, which could reduce the class test duration by about 80%.</p>

deepthi
2023-11-01 13:58:17

question: I am new to cucumber testing, i saw some examples in my teams github repo. Can we write scenarios in this format Given-- Then -- when? or does it have to be Given -- then -- when?

xeger
2023-11-01 15:01:50

*Thread Reply:* Given/When/Then/And are synonyms. The text that follows word #1 identifies the step that Cucumber will execute, and word #1 is not relevant.

So, if I understand your question, the answer is: yes, you can use those four words in any order you like and Cucumber will behave the same way. Those words are there to make it easier for humans to read your scenario.

These two lists of steps are equivalent:

Then foo Given bar When baz Given foo When bar When baz

‚ù§Ô∏è deepthi
Bob Allen
2023-11-02 17:09:56

*Thread Reply:* @xeger is correct, and, the https://www.google.com/search?scaesv=579007228&sxsrf=AM9HkKnc7CdYNQHXcCw2YdA65QWB8zXgw:1698969890424&q=asterisk&spell=1&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwj71bWGxKaCAxUgk4kEHZU7A1QQkeECKAB6BAgIEAE|asterisk is an equally valid placeholder that makes zero difference to the Cucumber parser. e.g. ** foo ** bar ** baz Exactly as Tony says, those specific words were chosen for the humans trying make sense of the intended behavior.

Add to this that there are multiple alternative sets of keywords as defined by ‚Ä¶ # language: > above the alternative language‚Äôs ‚ÄúFeature:‚Äù counterpart ‚Ä¶ can be used to allow all of the Gherkin keywords to be replaced by similar meaning words in any of 70+ languages including Pirate, Texas and emoji (not kidding).
